    <bioghist encodinganalog="545" id="a2">
      <head>Biographical Sketch</head>
      <p>A West Texas showman, oilman, and Texas legislator, Harley Sadler was
		  also an actor and tent show owner. He traveled through the United States in
		  tent shows during the period 1910 to 1944, primarily in Texas and the
		  Southwest. Elected to the Texas Senate in 1943, he served until his death in
		  1954.</p>
      <p>From the turn of the century through the era of the Great Depression,
		  tent shows were a popular medium of entertainment particularly in rural areas.
		  Harley Sadler and Harvey Haverstock were among the famous tent show owners in
		  Texas and the Southwest.</p>
      <p>The Handbook of Texas has published a more in-depth online biography
		  of Harley Herman Sadler at
		  http://www.tsha.utexas.edu/handbook/online/search.html</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520" id="a3">
      <head>Scope and Contents</head>
      <p>The collection contains genealogical materials on the Sadler family,
		  playbills and scripts from performances, artifacts, index cards of various
		  plays, and news clippings. All deal with the tent show career of Harley Sadler
		  and his wife, Billie. Some items are available on microfilm.</p>
    </scopecontent>
